glosses: to skip, jump lightly and quickly
to ricochet; (for a stone) to skip (over water)
to fail to occur properly or on time

etymology:
From Ottoman Turkish سكمك (sekmek, “to hop, hobble along, ricochet”), from Proto-Turkic *sēk- (“to jump”).
Cognate with Azerbaijani səkmək (“to hop”), Chuvash сикме (sikme, “to jump”). Compare Hungarian szökik (“to hop”).
